  "instructions": [
    "Heat butter and oil in a large pot over medium heat until melted.",
    "Add the diced chicken and brown on all sides for about 5 minutes, then remove and set aside.",
    "Sauté the chopped onion in the same pot until translucent, about 3 minutes.",
    "Stir in minced garlic, ginger, curry powder, turmeric, cumin, and pepper, cooking for 1 minute until fragrant.",
    "Return the chicken to the pot and pour in coconut milk, chicken broth, tamarind paste, fish sauce, and lime juice, then bring to a gentle boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes until the chicken is tender.",
    "Stir in the sour cream and dried basil, adjust seasoning with salt, and heat through for 5 minutes.",
    "Garnish with fresh cilantro before serving."
  ],
